      "content": "**Key structural elements**\n- **No strongly basic amine:**  \n  - The only nitrogens are **amide-like**: one **carbamate/urethane** (`NC(=O)O\u2026`) and one **lactam (amide) N** in a cyclic amide (`C(=O)N1\u2026`).  \n  - Both are **strongly resonance-stabilized** and are **not appreciably protonated at pH 7.4** (i.e., not a typical cationic hERG-binding center).\n- **Hydrophobic/aromatic domains (present):**\n  - **Two aryl rings**: one **phenyl** and one **difluorophenyl** (lipophilic, \u03c0-systems).\n  - A **bulky tert-butyl-like** fragment (`CC(C)(C)\u2026`) increasing hydrophobicity.\n- **Ring system / shape:**\n  - A **5-membered unsaturated lactam** (enamide-like) fused to substituents; fairly rigid and **conformationally constrained**.\n- **H-bonding / polarity:**\n  - **Two carbonyls** (carbamate + lactam) and an **ether/alcohol tail** (`OCCO`), adding polarity and H-bonding capacity.",
